%TUTORIAL -------------  DATASET MANAGEMENT FACILITY  -----------------
%OPTION  ===>_ZCMD
+
%                   -------------------------------------
                    ×   DSM "REPLACE" PRIMARY COMMAND   ×
                    -------------------------------------
+
    The REPLACE command allows a user to copy the current list of datase
    into a special save area. The replace function will replace the list
    it already exist. The COPY function can then be used to retrieved th
    saved dsn list.

%   REPLACE label

+   will save the list of datasets as list "label" where "label" is from
+   one to three bytes.
+
+   REPLACE can be abreviated as REP.
+
)PROC
   &ZUP = DSNHMGF
)END
